tags.inscription:
Prison A Wing (1852-56)
Modelled on Pentonville prison, a central space was surrounded by 150 identical cells each housing a single prisoner, held in isolation. When it closed in 1996 up to 3 men shared a cell. In 2006 it opened as a Hotel.
tags.name: Prison A Wing

tags.inscription: This tower was built to imprison debtors who owed money. A rare triangular stone staircase leads to four floors divided into cells, some with fireplaces. Prisoners remained in prison until they paid their debts, and long stays were common.
tags.name: Prison Debtors' Tower

tags.inscription: The wall is built close to a stream using large stones with a rubble inner core and smaller loose stones above, and, later razor wire. All this made escape underneath or over the wall very difficult.
tags.name: The Perimeter Wall at Oxford Prison

tags.inscription: In 2003 excavations uncovered the Castle Ditch part of the defences of the Norman Castle. 64 human skeletons were found buried here, many dating from the late 16th century.

tags.inscription:
Vaulted Well Chamber (13th century)
The Chamber houses a 54 feet deep brick-faced well which drops to the water level below the Mound. This provided a supply of fresh water to the occupants of the Tower which once stood on the summit of the Mound.
